        "thesis_family": "hypothesis_xs_minimal_v4_h5d",
        "market_mechanism": "Phase 1a multi-timescale extension of xs_minimal_v3 (v83). Same 4 v83 factor families (realized vol, intraday vol, distance to 20d high, coinglass top-trader long pct), but each averaged across 3 time scales (5d/20d/60d) before linear combination. Hypothesis: averaging across scales reduces single-window measurement noise, lifts rank IC modestly above v83 0.20 and improves walk-forward stability. This is Phase 1a in docs/quant_research/00_roadmap_state/strategy_upgrade_roadmap.md.",
        "directional_claim": "rank top-20 liquid perp-covered names by 4-family multi-timescale linear z-score; 12 raw factor columns (4 families x 3 scales) collapsed to 4 family means, then -0.30/-0.25/+0.25/-0.20 weights matching v83. Expected: rank IC >= 0.22, walk-forward median sharpe >= 1.1, regime worst >= -2.5 (modest improvements over v83).",
        "universe_rule": {
          "preset": "liquid_perp_core_20"
        },
        "dataset_profile": "cross_sectional_daily_4h",
        "execution_venue": "spot",
        "requires_derivatives_features": true,
        "minimum_executable_history_days": 180,
        "minimum_executable_coverage_ratio": 0.85,
        "required_feature_columns": [
